In their work, scientists come to new ́improved ́ compounds, prepared on the basis of the knowledge of the molecular mechanism of their binding to the virus protein.
The metalocarborans have a unique three-dimensional structure: two multifaceted cages consisting of bore, hydrogen and carbon atoms and coupled with a metal atom, in this case cobalt.
